details.description:
Anatolia Cafe & Cuisine
Get ready to experience the rich flavors of the Mediterranean! Anatolia Cafe & Cuisine brings you authentic Turkish and Mediterranean dishes, from savory kebabs to freshly baked pastries, paired with aromatic coffee and teas. We use only the finest ingredients to create a warm, inviting dining experience.

📍 1520 Overland Park Dr. Suite 107, Charlotte, NC 28262
We can’t wait to welcome you! Stay tuned for our grand opening and follow us for updates.

🍽️ Authentic Mediterranean & Turkish Cuisine

reviews_data.review_text: The appetizer plate was very nice and fresh, especially the Adana kebabs were very good, I can say that I felt myself in a special place, the place was spacious, clean and the employees were smiling, I can say that I got a quality service.

Overall, It was a great experience. They have authentic Mediterranean bakery and kebabs. The place is stunning.

I love it !
The lahmacun was super. It is fresh and amazing. I will be come back:)
Ilayda was very nice and sweet! She was extremely helpful and professional. I love a good service makes me enjoy coming to the restaurant. Food was great!!!

We had an absolutely wonderful experience at this charming café! From the moment we walked in, the atmosphere was inviting and full of good energy. Mehmet, the owner, was present and attentive throughout our visit, making sure every guest was well taken care of. It’s rare to see that kind of hands-on hospitality these days, and it truly made a difference.

Our server, İlayda, was a delight! Her energy and personality were radiant—she made us feel welcomed and cared for. It’s clear she loves what she does, and it added so much joy to our dining experience.

The cuisine was fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. You can tell a lot of heart goes into everything here. Highly recommend for anyone looking for both quality food and exceptional service!

Very small kaydaif piece costs $12. I mean, it's a good amount tiramisu from the steakhouse also goes for $12, even with the ice cream on the side the cost doesn’t make sense. The coffee was too sweet, and the espresso felt watered down. Ice latte felt like half water, half milk. On the ok side, the other breads were pretty good
Everyone is so nice and welcoming. The pastries and coffee are great. 10/10 would recommend to anyone in town.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks you so much for your kind words Olivia!

reviews_data.review_text: Great music and great people
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Michel! Thank you! We are glad you enjoyed the atmosphere and the good! We hope to see you again.

reviews_data.review_text: We went on opening day and were so impressed by the food, the atmosphere, the service- authentic Turkish food and so delicious!! We loved the pistachio cheesecake 😍
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your kind words Sinan! We hope to see you soon again!

reviews_data.review_text: This café and restaurant is truly a gem—one of the best spots in Charlotte, NC! The food is absolutely delicious, with a menu full of Mediterranean bakery, desserts, and dishes that feature a unique Turkish twist. The decor is stylish yet cozy, and the music adds the perfect touch to the relaxing atmosphere. The staff are incredibly friendly, and the service is always top-notch. It’s quickly become my favorite place in town, and I’ll definitely be recommending it to all my family and friends!

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your kind words Layth! We are glad you enjoyed the food and the atmosphere. We hope to see you soon again!

reviews_data.review_text: Very clean place and the food is soo amazing highly recommend to anyone who love Turkish food
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your kind words Amar!

reviews_data.review_text: We visited this new place today. Everything was amazing, food, people, owners, server. We will definitely be back, and recommend to everyone we know! Keep up the good work.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Feride! We are glad you had a good experience. We hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful space with really kind staff. Loved it, I’ll have to come back to try more of the food.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Deira for your kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: Went on opening day! 4/20. The pastries were phenomenal and Turkish coffee was awesome. The aesthetic is beautiful. They’ve done the best with the place aesthetically. Way nicer than Nona’s bakery or Jazzy Cheesecakes if you remember when those establishments occupied the space. I will def come here regularly. 10 out of 10
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Nathalie! Thank you for your kinda words! Come back again anytime!

reviews_data.review_text: I was the first customer this morning… Very delicious food.. Must try!!! Food finished before i could take one photo…
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your kind words Veziroglum! We hope to see you soon again!
